TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeRouteView
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
             Combines the behaviors of <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeView" /> and <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.RouteView" />,
             so that it displays the page matching the specified route but only if the user
             is authorized to see it.
            
             Additionally, this component supplies a cascading parameter of type <see cref="T:System.Threading.Tasks.Task`1" />,
             which makes the user's current authentication state available to descendants.
             </summary>

            </summary>

            </summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PreferExactMatches
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a flag to indicate whether route matching should prefer exact matches
            over wildcards.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            <para>
            Important: all applications should explicitly set this to true. The option to set it to false
            (or leave unset, which defaults to false) is only provided for backward compatibility.
            In .NET 6, this option will be removed and the router will always prefer exact matches.
            </para>
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Validation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A validation func or a validation attribute. Supported types are:
            <![CDATA[Func<T, bool>]]> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false
            <![CDATA[Func<T, string>]]> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null
            <![CDATA[Func<T, IEnumerable<string>>]]> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty
            <![CDATA[Func<T, Task<bool>>]]> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false
            <![CDATA[Func<T, Task<string>>]]> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null
            <![CDATA[Func<T, Task<IEnumerable<string>>>]]> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty
            System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.ValidationAttribute instances
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Validation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A validation func or a validation attribute. Supported types are:
            <![CDATA[Func<T, bool>]]> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false
            <![CDATA[Func<T, string>]]> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null
            <![CDATA[Func<T, IEnumerable<string>>]]> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty
            <![CDATA[Func<T, Task<bool>>]]> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false
            <![CDATA[Func<T, Task<string>>]]> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null
            <![CDATA[Func<T, Task<IEnumerable<string>>>]]> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty
            System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.ValidationAttribute instances
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: For
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specify an expression which returns the model's field for which validation messages should be displayed.
            Currently only string fields are supported.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: InfoFormat
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Format string for the display of the current page, which you can localize to your language. Available variables are:
            {first_item}, {last_item} and {all_items} which will replaced with the indices of the page's first and last item as well as the total number of items.
            Default: "{first_item}-{last_item} of {all_items}" which is transformed into "0-25 of 77". 
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Validation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A validation func or a validation attribute. Supported types are:
            <![CDATA[Func<T, bool>]]> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false
            <![CDATA[Func<T, string>]]> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null
            <![CDATA[Func<T, IEnumerable<string>>]]> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty
            <![CDATA[Func<T, Task<bool>>]]> ... will output the standard error message "Invalid" if false
            <![CDATA[Func<T, Task<string>>]]> ... outputs the result as error message, no error if null
            <![CDATA[Func<T, Task<IEnumerable<string>>>]]> ... outputs all the returned error messages, no error if empty
            System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.ValidationAttribute instances
            </summary>

<summary>
            User class names, separated by space
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Style
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            User styles, applied on top of the component's own classes and styles
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Tag
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Use Tag to attach any user data object to the component for your convenience.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: UserAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            UserAttributes carries all attributes you add to the component that don't match any of its parameters. They
            will be splatted onto the underlying HTML tag.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: T
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the type of the type parameter T for the MudBlazor.MudTable<T> component.

BoundAttributes.Name: RowTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines how a table row looks like. Use MudTd to define the table cells and their content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowEditingTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines how a table row looks like in edit mode (for selected row). Use MudTd to define the table cells and their content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Items
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data to display in the table. MudTable will render one row per item
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Filter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A function that returns whether or not an item should be displayed in the table. You can use this to implement your own search function.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnRowClick
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Button click event.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItem
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Returns the item which was last clicked on in single selection mode (that is, if MultiSelection is false)
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItemChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Callback is called when a row has been clicked and returns the selected item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItems
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If MultiSelection is true, this returns the currently selected items. You can bind this property and the initial content of the HashSet you bind it to will cause these rows to be selected initially.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItemsChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Callback is called whenever items are selected or deselected in multi selection mode.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ServerData
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Supply an async function which (re)loads filtered, paginated and sorted data from server.
            Table will await this func and update based on the returned TableData.
            Used only with ServerData
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Elevation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The higher the number, the heavier the drop-shadow. 0 for no shadow.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Square
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true to disable rounded corners
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Dense
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true for rows with a narrow height
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Hover
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set true to see rows hover on mouse-over.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Breakpoint
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            At what breakpoint the table should switch to mobile layout. Takes Sm, Md, Lg and Xl the default behavior is breaking on Xs.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FixedHeader
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true, the header will stay in place when the table is scrolled. Note: set Height to make the table scrollable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Setting a height will allow to scroll the table. If not set, it will try to grow in height. You can set this to any CSS value that the
            attribute 'height' accepts, i.e. 500px. 
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SortLabel
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If table is in smalldevice mode and uses any kind of sorting the text applied here will be the sort selects label.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowsPerPage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If the table has more items than this number, it will break the rows into pages of said size.
            Note: requires a MudTablePager in PagerContent.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CurrentPage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The page index of the currently displayed page. Usually called by MudTablePager.
            Note: requires a MudTablePager in PagerContent.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MultiSelection
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set to true to enable selection of multiple rows with check boxes. 
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ToolBarContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Optional. Add any kind of toolbar to this render fragment.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HeaderContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add MudTh cells here to define the table header.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ColGroup
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a group of one or more columns in a table for formatting.
            Ex:
            table
                colgroup
                   col span="2" style="background-color:red"
                   col style="background-color:yellow"
                 colgroup
                 header
                 body
            table
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PagerContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add MudTablePager here to enable breaking the rows in to multiple pages.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnCommitEditClick
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Button click event.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CommitEditCommand
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Command executed when the user clicks on the CommitEdit Button.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CommitEditCommandParameter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Command parameter for the CommitEdit Button. By default, will be the row level item model, if you won't set anything else.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CommitEditTooltip
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Tooltip for the CommitEdit Button.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TotalItems
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Number of items. Used only with ServerData="true"
            </summary>

<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting elements containing attributes with URL expected values.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Resolves URLs starting with '~/' (relative to the application's 'webroot' setting) that are not
            targeted by other <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" />s. Runs prior to other <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" />s to ensure
            application-relative URLs are resolved.</remarks>

TagHelpers.Name: Bind
TagHelpers.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributes.Name: @bind-...

For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: format

BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the event handler name to attach for change notifications for the value provided by the '@bind-...' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: culture
